                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <p>Original sewing on seven split thongs, entering the original wood boards through their outer faces, the boards with cushioned edges; the upper and lower pastedowns show evidence of a pair of strap-and-pin clasps, the pins towards the middle of the lower board; the boards coverd with polished brown leather, blind-tooled with simple fillets; the spine with a 20th-century black leather title piece lettered in gilt 'M. S. S. | NEWENHAM | ABBEY | DEVON', and with an uncharacteristic 19th-century paper label inscribed with the Phillipps number: '+25088'</p>
